Installation:

- Create a mySQL database and execute as mysql admin:

  mysql> CREATE DATABASE phtagr;
  mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON phtagr.* TO 'phtagr'@'localhost' \
      IDENTIFIED BY '<PASSWD>'; 

- Checkout the new branch from svn to a webbrowser directory like
  ~/.public_html or /var/www

  $ svn checkout svn://inspirationslos.de/phtagr/trunk/phtagr

- Create a phTagr data directory. Eg. /var/www/phtagr-data. This directory is
  used for cached image data or uploaded images. For security reasons, this
  folder should be writeable by the webserver process but not accessable by the
  browser.

  $ mkdir -p /var/www/phtagr-data
  $ chmod 775 /var/www/phtagr-data
  $ chgrp www-data /var/www/phtar-data

- Open the phTagr URL from the browser and follow the installtion link.
  - Enter the phTagr data directory
  - Enter the mysql data
  - Copy the var.inc file from the phTagr data directory to the phtagr
    subdirectory which contains all the php objects
  - Create admin account (account name must be "admin")

